HEADWORD: Lunulet
<hw>Lu"nu*let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>lunule</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small spot, shaped
like a half-moon or crescent; <as>as, the <ex>lunulet</ex> on the wings
of many insects</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

